b-link/append.description: router-link prop: Setting append prop always appends the relative path to the current path

b-link/replace.description: router-link prop: Setting the replace prop will call 'router.replace()' instead of 'router.push()' when clicked, so the navigation will not leave a history record

b-table/head-row-variant.description: Apply a Bootstrap theme color variant to the tr element in the thead

b-table/thead-class.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the thead element

b-table/thead-tr-class.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the tr element in the thead

b-table/foot-clone.description: Enable to the footer of the table, and clone the header content by default

b-table/foot-variant.description: Footer variant: 'light' or 'dark', or unset. May take precedence over foot-row-variant

b-table/foot-row-variant.description: Apply a Bootstrap theme color variant to the tr element in the tfoot. Falls back to head-row-variant

b-table/tfoot-class.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the tfoot element

b-table/tfoot-tr-class.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the tr element in the tfoot

b-table/tbody-tr-class.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the tr element in the tbody. Can be a function that returns a class (see docs for details)

b-table/tbody-tr-attr.description: Attributes to be added to each tr in the tbody, or a function returning such attributes (see docs for details)

b-table/details-td-class.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the td element in the details row

b-table/tbody-transition-props.description: Vue 'transition-group' properties. When provided will make the tbody a Vue 'transition-group' component

b-table/tbody-transition-handlers.description: Vue 'transition-group' event handlers. When provided will make the tbody a Vue 'transition-group' component

b-table/tbody-class.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the tbody element

b-table/filter.description: Criteria for filtering. Internal filtering supports only string or RegExpr criteria.

b-table/filter-function.description: Reference to a function to use instead of the internal filtering function. Refer to the docs for details

b-table/filter-ignored-fields.description: Array of top level fields to ignore when filtering the item data

b-table/filter-included-fields.description: Array of fields to include when filtering. Overrides filter-ignore-fields

b-table/filter-debounce.description: Time in milliseconds to debounce changes to the filter criteria before filtering the records

b-table/sort-by.description: Field name that is currently being sorted. Set to null to clear sorting. Syncable with the .sync prop modifier

b-table/sort-desc.description: Set to true to sort the column in descending order. Syncable with the .sync prop modifier

b-table/sort-direction.description: The initial sorting direction to sort an unsorted column by: 'asc', 'desc', or 'last' (to use the previous sort direction)

b-table/sort-compare.description: A reference to a function for sort-comparing tow rows of data. Defaults to the internal sort compare routine. See docs for details

b-table/sort-compare-options.description: An object containing sort configuration for the 'String.prototype.sortLocale' method. See docs for details

b-table/sort-compare-locale.description: The locale string (or array of locale string) that specified the language when sorting. See docs for details

b-table/sort-null-last.description: When sorting, null and undefined values will be sorted first (or last, depending on 'sort-desc'). Set this prop to sort null values last. Only applicable to internal sorting

b-table/no-sort-reset.description: When a table is sortable, clicking on any non-sortable column heading will clear the current sort values. Set this prop to disable this feature

b-table/label-sort-asc.description: Hidden string to place in the header cell when clicking the cell will change the sort direction to ascending

b-table/label-sort-desc.description: Hidden string to place in the header cell when clicking the cell will change the sort direction to descending

b-table/label-sort-clear.description: Hidden string to place in the header cell when clicking the cell will clear the current sorting direction

b-table/no-local-sorting.description: Disabled the internal sorting routine, and expects the user to provde the items sorted. Sorting controls will still be available

b-table/no-footer-sorting.description: When the build in formatter is used, setting this prop will disable the sorting ability in the footer

b-table/sort-icon-left.description: Positions the sort control to the left of the header text. Default is on the right of the header text

b-table/per-page.description: Number of rows to show per page. Set to 0 to disable pagination

b-table/current-page.description: The current page number to display when the table is paginated. Starting from 1 and up

b-table/caption.description: Text string to place in the caption element

b-table/caption-html.description: HTML string to place in the caption element. Use with caution

b-table/selectable.description: When set, places the table body rows in selectable mode

b-table/select-mode.description: The selectable mode for the table when 'selectable' is set. Possible values: 'single', 'multi' or 'range'

b-table/selected-variant.description: Bootstrap color theme variant to set selected rows to. Use any of the standard Bootstrap theme color variants, or the special table row variant 'active' (default). Set to an empty string to not use a variant

b-table/no-select-on-click.description: Disables row selection via click events. Row selection will be only available programmatically

b-table/show-empty.description: When enabled, and there are no item records to show, shows a message that there are no rows to show

b-table/empty-text.description: Text string to show when the table has no items to show

b-table/empty-html.description: HTML string to show when the table has no items to show. Use with caution

b-table/empty-filtered-text.description: Text string to show when the table has no items to show due to filtering

b-table/empty-filtered-html.description: HTML string to show when the table has no items to show due to filtering. Use with caution

b-table/busy.description: When set, forces the table into the busy state.Automatically set when an items provider function is being called

b-table/no-provider-paging.description: When set, uses internal paging to pagination the data. Otherwise the items provider is expected to perform the paging

b-table/no-provider-sorting.description: When set, uses internal sorting to sort the data. Otherwise the items provider is expected to perform the sorting

b-table/no-provider-filtering.description: When set, uses internal filtering to pagination the data. Otherwise the provider is expected to perform the filtering

b-table/api-url.description: Pass through prop. Passed as part of the context object sent to the items provider function

b-table-lite/fields.description: Array of field names or array of field definition objects

b-table-lite/primary-key.description: Name of a table field that contains a guaranteed unique value per row. Needed for tbody transition support, and also speeds up table rendering

b-table-lite/value.description: Currently displayed row data. Read-only. Do not set a value on this prop

b-table-lite/striped.description: Applies striping to the tbody rows

b-table-lite/bordered.description: Adds borders to all the cells and headers

b-table-lite/outlined.description: Adds an outline border to the table element

b-table-lite/dark.description: Places the table in dark mode

b-table-lite/small.description: Renders the table with smaller cell padding

b-table-lite/fixed.description: Makes all columns equal width (fixed layout table). Will speed up rendering for large tables. Column widths can be set via CSS or colgroup

b-table-lite/responsive.description: Makes the table responsive in width, adding a horizontal scrollbar. Set to true for always responsive or set to one of the breakpoints to switch from responsive to normal: 'sm', 'md', 'lg', 'xl'

b-table-lite/sticky-header.description: Makes the table header sticky. Set to true for a maximum height 300px tall table, or set to any valid CSS hight (including units)

b-table-lite/no-border-collapse.description: Disable's the collapsing of table borders. Useful when table has sticky headers or columns

b-table-lite/caption-top.description: Visually place the table caption above the table. Default is below.

b-table-lite/table-variant.description: Apply a Bootstrap theme color variant to the entire table

b-toast/append-toast.description: When true, the toast will be appended to the bottom on the visible toasts, otherwise it will be prepended

b-toast/no-auto-hide.description: When set, disabled the toast from automatically dismissing itself

b-toast/solid.description: When set, renderes the toast with a solid background rather than translucent

b-toast/header-class.description: CSS class (or classes) to add to the toast header element

b-toast/body-class.description: CSS class (or classes) to add to the toast body element

b-toast/href.description: Denotes the target URL of the link for standard a links

b-toast/to.description: router-link prop: Denotes the target route of the link. When clicked, the value of the to prop will be passed to router.push() internally, so the value can be either a string or a Location descriptor object

b-toast/static.description: Renders the content of the component in-place in the DOM, rather than portalling it to be appended to the body element

b-toaster/aria-atomic.description: When screen reader's should read out the entire contents (set to string 'true') or just the changes (set to string 'false'). Leave blank for most cases

b-toaster/role.description: Sets the ARIA attribute 'role' to a specific value

b-tooltip/placement.description: Placement of the tooltip: One of 'top', 'bottom', 'right', 'left', 'top-left', 'top-right', 'bottom-left', 'bottom-right', 'left-top', 'left-bottom', 'right-top', 'right-bottom'

b-tooltip/fallback-placement.description: placement to use when the tooltip would be out of boundaries. Refer to the docs for more details

b-tooltip/variant.description: Applies one of the Bootstrap theme color variants to the component

b-tooltip/custom-class.description: CSS class (or classes) to apply to the tooltip's root element

v-b-toggle.description: Easily toggle content visibility on your pages. Includes support for making accordions.

v-b-modal.description: Modals are streamlined, but flexible dialog prompts powered by JavaScript and CSS. They support a number of use cases from user notification to completely custom content and feature a handful of helpful sub-components, sizes, variants, accessibility, and more.

v-b-popover.description: Add BootstrapVue popovers to any element on your site, using Bootstrap v4 CSS for styling and animations. Popovers are tooltips on steroids.

v-b-scrollspy.description: Automatically activate BootstrapVue navigation or list group components based on scroll position to indicate which link is currently active in the viewport.

v-b-tooltip.description: Add custom BootstrapVue tooltips to any element. Tooltips can be triggered by hovering, focusing, or clicking an element.

v-b-visible.description: The `v-b-visible` directive allows you to react when an element becomes visible in the viewport.
